      <scopecontent id="aspace_1006106c61e64edd1d9695616c01f4d1">
         <head>Content Description</head>
         <p>The collection includes 183 lantern slides used for lectures on the history of medicine that were transferred to the Medical Historical Library at an unknown date. Slides are black and white images from manuscripts, printed materials, and works of art related to the history of medicine. Many of the slides are labeled "Made by James Huntington, 610 St. John's Place, Brooklyn, N. Y."</p>
      </scopecontent>
